data.content:
Here are the four files created in `Components/`:

| File | Role |
|------|------|
| `Order.cs` | Models (`ShippingInfo`, `PaymentInfo`, `Order`) |
| `CheckoutWizard.razor` | Parent wizard — tracks active step, owns `Order` state, exposes `OnOrderPlaced` callback |
| `ShippingStep.razor` | Step 1 — binds shipping fields, validates Name/Address are non-empty before allowing "Next" |
| `PaymentStep.razor` | Step 2 — binds payment fields, has "Back" and "Place Order" buttons |

**Usage example:**

```razor
<CheckoutWizard OnOrderPlaced="HandleOrder" />

@code {
    private void HandleOrder(Order order)
    {
        // order.Shipping and order.Payment are populated
    }
}
```

The wizard flows: Shipping → (validates Name & Address) → Payment → "Place Order" fires `OnOrderPlaced` with the completed `Order`.
